SECTION 4: SOFT THRESHOLD — SMOOTH DECOUPLING
----------------------------------------------------------------------

  Physical decoupling: a heavy particle of mass M_VL
  contributes to the running as a smooth function of mu/M_VL.
  The step function is an approximation.

  Smooth threshold function:
    f(mu) = ln(1 + mu^2/M_VL^2) / ln(1 + mu_GUT^2/M_VL^2)
  This gives f -> 0 for mu << M_VL and f -> 1 for mu >> M_VL.
  The effective betas are: b_i(mu) = b_SM + f(mu)*db_VL
  and bij(mu) = bij_SM + f(mu)*dbij_VL

  Soft threshold results (M_GUT ~ 4.1e+15 GeV):

  M_VL(GeV)      alpha_s   miss(%%)
  -------- ------------ ----------
       200   0.10957027     7.1438
       500   0.10749754     8.9004
      1000   0.10588295    10.2687
      2000   0.10430004    11.6101
      4000   0.10276177    12.9138

  No-threshold: miss = 0.3251%

  Best soft threshold: M_VL = 200 GeV, miss = 7.1438%

